The paper deals with automated symbolic analysis of e-voting protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of conditions to guarantee ballot secrecy, which involves logical reasoning and formal methods (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of ProVerif, a tool for cryptographic protocol verification, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of verification, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
